00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:49,696 --> 00:00:51,072
<i>It's not plausible,</i>

2
00:00:51,781 --> 00:00:53,158
<i>nor is it possible.</i>

3
00:00:54,159 --> 00:00:55,326
<i>I had a feeling,</i>

4
00:00:56,494 --> 00:00:57,537
<i>but how are you…</i>

5
00:01:05,378 --> 00:01:06,588
Master.

6
00:01:58,765 --> 00:02:02,435
THE WONDERFOOLS

7
00:02:03,728 --> 00:02:08,107
EPISODE 5
ALL WE NEED IS YOU

8
00:02:38,137 --> 00:02:41,808
I told you to find the Child of Eternity,
not to cause trouble.

9
00:02:44,352 --> 00:02:46,521
I merely showed more signs of the end.

10
00:02:46,604 --> 00:02:48,898
To who? Number 3972?

11
00:02:50,191 --> 00:02:51,317
Pal-ho, don't tell me…

12
00:02:52,402 --> 00:02:54,737
Are you worried
that he'll find the child first?

13
00:02:54,821 --> 00:02:57,657
Shut your mouth
before I hurl you through the ceiling.

14
00:02:57,740 --> 00:02:59,742
What? Do you think I'd just sit back?

15
00:02:59,826 --> 00:03:02,287
I told you both
not to use your powers recklessly!

16
00:03:02,787 --> 00:03:05,415
I've already told you
we'd be in danger if we get…

17
00:03:10,253 --> 00:03:12,213
Even if you get angry, control yourself.

18
00:03:12,755 --> 00:03:15,091
Just until Father finds the cure, okay?

19
00:03:19,220 --> 00:03:20,555
Ho-ran, you too.

20
00:03:21,264 --> 00:03:22,932
Stop it and apologize to Pal-ho.

21
00:03:25,059 --> 00:03:25,893
Sorry.

22
00:03:37,113 --> 00:03:40,074
Do you think
that bastard will come back to us?

23
00:03:41,492 --> 00:03:43,119
It's not like he has anyone else.

24
00:03:43,703 --> 00:03:46,664
Why are you always so lenient
with that jerk?

25
00:03:49,751 --> 00:03:50,877
Because he's cute.

26
00:05:04,033 --> 00:05:05,868
It doesn't hurt at all now, does it?

27
00:05:20,007 --> 00:05:21,467
<i>Because he smiled.</i>

28
00:05:23,261 --> 00:05:24,929
<i>He only smiled…</i>

29
00:05:26,889 --> 00:05:28,182
<i>when he was with me.</i>

30
00:05:46,242 --> 00:05:49,245
How does he have absolutely nothing?

31
00:05:49,996 --> 00:05:50,997
Nothing important.

32
00:05:51,581 --> 00:05:53,249
Nothing that holds any memories.

33
00:05:53,332 --> 00:05:54,750
This is really it?

34
00:05:55,251 --> 00:05:58,129
Maybe it's because
he's only staying here temporarily.

35
00:05:59,672 --> 00:06:02,467
Still, don't people usually
at least have a photo?

36
00:06:04,385 --> 00:06:05,636
Unit 203!

37
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:07,221
Being noisy again!

38
00:06:07,305 --> 00:06:09,348
I can hear you dragging your chair!

39
00:06:16,105 --> 00:06:18,399
Chae-ni! I really can't do this by myself!

40
00:06:18,483 --> 00:06:19,358
Help me!

41
00:06:30,328 --> 00:06:31,329
What's all this?

42
00:06:31,829 --> 00:06:33,581
He's covered in scars, Chae-ni!

43
00:06:41,422 --> 00:06:42,381
<i>So,</i>

44
00:06:42,965 --> 00:06:45,092
who did you say attacked you guys?

45
00:06:46,010 --> 00:06:48,137
Wunderkinder, yeah.

46
00:06:48,221 --> 00:06:49,931
Yes, they were called Wunderkinder.

47
00:06:50,014 --> 00:06:51,974
-Wunderkinder?
-Wunderkinder.

48
00:06:52,475 --> 00:06:54,185
Wunderkinder.

49
00:06:54,685 --> 00:06:56,103
That sounds pretty cool.

50
00:06:57,396 --> 00:07:00,816
Then, are we Wunderkinder too?

51
00:07:01,442 --> 00:07:03,361
No, he called us defects.

52
00:07:04,487 --> 00:07:07,073
Who are they calling defective?
Unbelievable!

53
00:07:07,573 --> 00:07:10,660
Are they saying
they're industry standard or what?

54
00:07:14,121 --> 00:07:16,374
Anyway, industry standard or defective,

55
00:07:16,874 --> 00:07:19,085
it means experiments <i>were </i>conducted,
doesn't it?

56
00:07:20,753 --> 00:07:24,674
So the reason that pigeon blinked sideways
and the carp winked at me

57
00:07:25,174 --> 00:07:26,842
was their illegal experiments?

58
00:07:28,636 --> 00:07:29,470
Phenol!

59
00:07:29,554 --> 00:07:31,222
So they dumped the phenol too?

60
00:07:31,305 --> 00:07:32,974
I don't know.

61
00:07:33,474 --> 00:07:36,394
Anyway, I'm terrified.
We can't even report them to the cops.

62
00:07:40,147 --> 00:07:41,232
Is that so?

63
00:07:42,024 --> 00:07:45,319
And she won't say
what happened at the vacant lot?

64
00:07:45,403 --> 00:07:48,489
No, so I'm trying to find out on my own.

65
00:07:49,073 --> 00:07:51,409
Anyway, I'm glad that Chae-ni is safe.

66
00:07:52,702 --> 00:07:55,871
Make sure to report straight to me
if anything happens to you.

67
00:07:56,372 --> 00:07:58,124
If you smell danger, just back off.

68
00:07:58,207 --> 00:08:00,626
Yes, Grandma. Don't worry.

69
00:08:42,668 --> 00:08:44,337
What kind of life

70
00:08:45,171 --> 00:08:46,881
have you lived up until now?

71
00:08:57,058 --> 00:08:57,892
Don't…

72
00:08:59,894 --> 00:09:01,896
Don't what? You're filthy.

73
00:09:06,192 --> 00:09:07,026
Don't…

74
00:09:10,821 --> 00:09:12,573
A clean freak even in your sleep…

75
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:15,618
Fine.

76
00:09:15,701 --> 00:09:17,328
I'll get you a wet towel.

77
00:09:36,764 --> 00:09:37,932
Don't go,

78
00:09:39,642 --> 00:09:40,685
Mom.

79
00:09:44,230 --> 00:09:46,065
You said you didn't have a mom.

80
00:09:52,071 --> 00:09:54,740
I don't have a prickly son
like you either!

81
00:10:00,162 --> 00:10:01,330
I'm scared.

82
00:10:04,375 --> 00:10:05,960
<i>No, don't.</i>

83
00:10:06,043 --> 00:10:07,169
<i>One more time!</i>

84
00:10:07,253 --> 00:10:08,254
I'm scared.

85
00:10:08,337 --> 00:10:09,171
<i>Please stop.</i>

86
00:10:09,255 --> 00:10:12,341
<i>-Please, we're here!</i>
<i>-It hurts. Please stop.</i>

87
00:11:12,318 --> 00:11:13,778
A grown man, crying?

88
00:11:16,447 --> 00:11:18,032
You may not have a mom,

89
00:11:18,741 --> 00:11:20,284
but you turned out fine.

90
00:11:33,047 --> 00:11:34,006
Eunie, hold it!

91
00:11:38,552 --> 00:11:40,471
Are you okay? Did anything happen?

92
00:11:42,139 --> 00:11:43,641
What kind of anything?

93
00:11:46,852 --> 00:11:49,021
It's the northern lights.

94
00:11:50,439 --> 00:11:52,733
If you mean anything ordinary, no.

95
00:11:52,817 --> 00:11:56,111
Anything is anything.
What's anything ordinary?

96
00:11:57,238 --> 00:11:58,072
Where are you off to?

97
00:12:00,157 --> 00:12:01,116
I have some business!

98
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:03,160
Stay home!

99
00:12:03,661 --> 00:12:05,663
That crazy girl.

100
00:12:52,376 --> 00:12:53,794
<i>Make sure you take these.</i>

101
00:13:52,436 --> 00:13:57,232
HERE TO HELP

102
00:14:01,695 --> 00:14:03,113
Hey.

103
00:14:03,197 --> 00:14:05,616
Those industry standards or Wunderkinder,

104
00:14:05,699 --> 00:14:07,743
can't we just find evidence
and report them?

105
00:14:07,826 --> 00:14:09,662
It wouldn't even be anonymous.

106
00:14:09,745 --> 00:14:12,414
No, thanks. What if they retaliate?

107
00:14:12,498 --> 00:14:15,417
But there's no reward money
for anonymous tips!

108
00:14:17,878 --> 00:14:19,630
From what I hear,

109
00:14:20,130 --> 00:14:22,967
several reports were made,
but the cops never found anything.

110
00:14:23,050 --> 00:14:24,677
We need to bring them evidence.

111
00:14:24,760 --> 00:14:27,012
And why do <i>we </i>have to be the ones
to do that?

112
00:14:27,096 --> 00:14:29,765
Who else would do it if not us?

113
00:14:32,226 --> 00:14:33,185
Have you forgotten?

114
00:14:33,686 --> 00:14:35,062
We've got powers.

115
00:14:35,145 --> 00:14:36,021
"We"? Please.

116
00:14:36,105 --> 00:14:38,649
What good are powers
if we don't know how to use them?

117
00:14:39,650 --> 00:14:43,112
Frankly speaking, how can we be sure
Mr. Oddball will help us?

118
00:14:46,031 --> 00:14:47,992
We'll know if we ask him.

119
00:15:37,583 --> 00:15:41,211
We get it, all right?
You're not exactly happy to see us.

120
00:15:41,962 --> 00:15:43,672
Then why did you show up here again?

121
00:15:44,173 --> 00:15:46,592
Because we still like you, Master.

122
00:15:47,092 --> 00:15:48,510
I wouldn't say I like you.

123
00:15:48,594 --> 00:15:51,930
I'd consider this
more of a strategic MOU relationship--

124
00:15:52,014 --> 00:15:54,641
You sure aren't shy
about telling people you like them.

125
00:15:54,725 --> 00:15:58,353
I'm not shy if I don't like people either.
Like, "I can't stand you, Mr. Son."

126
00:16:01,815 --> 00:16:03,567
I didn't help you because I wanted to.

127
00:16:04,234 --> 00:16:06,695
Most people don't bother
if they don't want to help.

128
00:16:06,779 --> 00:16:09,490
But even if you don't want to,
you help in the end.

129
00:16:09,990 --> 00:16:11,033
Know why?

130
00:16:13,911 --> 00:16:15,621
Because you're on my side.

131
00:16:15,704 --> 00:16:18,874
Right, Master? You can't deny it now.
You're on our side.

132
00:16:19,708 --> 00:16:20,667
Says who?

133
00:16:21,418 --> 00:16:23,837
I say you're on my side.
Got a problem with that?

134
00:16:24,338 --> 00:16:26,090
You don't have any friends anyway.

135
00:16:26,173 --> 00:16:28,509
What's wrong with having
some people in your corner?

136
00:16:28,592 --> 00:16:31,970
-Isn't that right, Kang Ro-bin?
-You only have one friend too.

137
00:16:32,054 --> 00:16:34,723
What do you mean, only one?
I have another right here!

138
00:16:34,807 --> 00:16:36,767
Get a grip. You think I'm your friend?

139
00:16:36,850 --> 00:16:39,645
Royal Nightmare,
you're complaining about being my friend?

140
00:16:40,854 --> 00:16:41,980
Keep pushing me, and--

141
00:16:42,064 --> 00:16:43,857
What are you, a button? Just hurry up.

142
00:16:43,941 --> 00:16:45,651
Hey, let go of me!

143
00:16:51,406 --> 00:16:52,366
You smiled…

144
00:16:58,038 --> 00:16:58,872
did you?

145
00:17:02,376 --> 00:17:04,086
I'm guessing you have questions.

146
00:17:06,088 --> 00:17:07,089
First, Wunderkinder.

147
00:17:08,382 --> 00:17:11,093
If you ever meet them, never engage.

148
00:17:11,176 --> 00:17:12,719
-Think we'd want to?
-Why not?

149
00:17:12,803 --> 00:17:15,180
-If they provoke us first--
-Sure, I've seen them--

150
00:17:15,264 --> 00:17:16,098
You'd die.

151
00:17:18,433 --> 00:17:19,434
You're outmatched.

152
00:17:20,310 --> 00:17:21,937
Of course.

153
00:17:22,020 --> 00:17:24,022
The guy I saw the other day went like this

154
00:17:25,107 --> 00:17:26,733
and crushed everything.

155
00:17:26,817 --> 00:17:29,319
I guess those kids are pretty violent.

156
00:17:29,403 --> 00:17:30,404
Then,

157
00:17:30,988 --> 00:17:32,781
you can help us stand a chance.

158
00:17:33,448 --> 00:17:36,577
Why is your first thought
to fight someone you don't even know?

159
00:17:36,660 --> 00:17:38,704
Well, they threw the first punch.

160
00:17:38,787 --> 00:17:41,248
They threw it at Master, not at us.

161
00:17:41,331 --> 00:17:43,959
Which means throwing it at us.
Whose side are you on?

162
00:17:44,042 --> 00:17:46,628
She just wants to beat up
whoever catches her eye.

163
00:17:46,712 --> 00:17:48,630
And I think someone just caught my eye.

164
00:17:48,714 --> 00:17:51,008
You cheeky little punk, I swear…

165
00:17:51,550 --> 00:17:53,051
Mr. Son, you gonna smack me?

166
00:17:53,135 --> 00:17:54,136
-Chae-ni.
-Hit me.

167
00:17:54,219 --> 00:17:56,013
-Can you handle the fallout?
-Hold up.

168
00:17:56,096 --> 00:17:58,348
-Can you handle it?
-To this day, I've never ever…

169
00:17:58,432 --> 00:17:59,850
-Not once…
-Chae-ni, please.

170
00:17:59,933 --> 00:18:01,226
I've never hit a woman.

171
00:18:01,310 --> 00:18:02,978
-Mr. Son, please.
-Gloves are off.

172
00:18:03,061 --> 00:18:04,813
Hey, stop butting me with your head.

173
00:18:04,897 --> 00:18:06,023
-Not once, but--
-I'll--

174
00:18:14,781 --> 00:18:17,117
Find your own secret switch.

175
00:18:17,701 --> 00:18:19,119
When your abilities activate,

176
00:18:19,203 --> 00:18:21,580
when your powers disappear,
and any other changes.

177
00:18:21,663 --> 00:18:23,874
If you start by taking note
of the small things,

178
00:18:23,957 --> 00:18:25,667
you'll eventually see a pattern.

179
00:18:25,751 --> 00:18:28,587
To find a pattern in a routine,

180
00:18:28,670 --> 00:18:32,341
we'll need a huge amount of data.

181
00:18:32,424 --> 00:18:33,967
Could you two even handle it?

182
00:18:35,636 --> 00:18:38,347
What about you, Mr. Son?
You speak as though you can.

183
00:18:40,766 --> 00:18:44,186
I think mine activates
when my heart races,

184
00:18:44,269 --> 00:18:46,605
but not much makes my heart race nowadays.

185
00:18:46,688 --> 00:18:48,440
I've been through so much nonsense.

186
00:18:49,316 --> 00:18:50,776
Nothing surprises me anymore.

187
00:18:50,859 --> 00:18:52,110
Nothing flusters me.

188
00:18:52,611 --> 00:18:54,947
I'm just so relaxed.

189
00:18:55,030 --> 00:18:56,907
Then, I'd say the next best thing is…

190
00:18:59,493 --> 00:19:00,744
Master!

191
00:19:02,871 --> 00:19:03,705
How about running?

192
00:19:05,207 --> 00:19:07,167
I've tried running in figures of eight.

193
00:19:08,585 --> 00:19:10,796
I was fine, just sweaty.

194
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:16,635
You have to cry?

195
00:19:16,718 --> 00:19:18,929
-Well, last time--
-Not cry from getting hit.

196
00:19:19,012 --> 00:19:20,764
-I don't think that's it.
-Guess not.

197
00:19:21,515 --> 00:19:25,060
I think my powers mostly activated
when I was with Mr. Son and Chae-ni.

198
00:19:25,143 --> 00:19:27,604
I'm telling you,
you need to be moved to tears.

199
00:19:27,688 --> 00:19:29,648
I've graced Kang Ro-bin

200
00:19:29,731 --> 00:19:33,277
with countless nuggets of wisdom
to live by, you know?

201
00:19:35,529 --> 00:19:36,363
Try it.

202
00:19:37,990 --> 00:19:39,366
You want me to do it now?

203
00:19:41,910 --> 00:19:43,912
How should I move him to tears?

204
00:19:47,666 --> 00:19:50,711
Word of advice from a wise man
who's lived longer than you.

205
00:19:50,794 --> 00:19:51,962
Sure.

206
00:19:52,921 --> 00:19:54,548
Don't live your life like that.

207
00:19:55,299 --> 00:19:58,218
Neither you nor Eun Chae-ni
have any vigor for life.

208
00:19:58,802 --> 00:20:02,556
Do the words "improvement" and "growth"
not exist in your vocabulary?

209
00:20:02,639 --> 00:20:03,849
Don't live like that.

210
00:20:03,932 --> 00:20:06,560
Without passion, life is just idling.

211
00:20:06,643 --> 00:20:08,770
Wanna peel onions all your life?

212
00:20:10,272 --> 00:20:11,273
That's it, yes.

213
00:20:11,898 --> 00:20:13,608
So? Do you feel moved?

214
00:20:13,692 --> 00:20:14,943
Yes, I'm annoyed.

215
00:20:15,027 --> 00:20:17,779
Hey, why are you annoyed
by an elder's sound advice?

216
00:20:17,863 --> 00:20:20,073
Sit. You're pissing me off
for no reason again.

217
00:20:20,157 --> 00:20:22,993
You think I'm a schmuck
because I hang out with you?

218
00:20:23,076 --> 00:20:26,997
Didn't I tell you I came first in Haeseong
in the National Academic Achievement Test?

219
00:20:27,622 --> 00:20:28,665
Then again,

220
00:20:28,749 --> 00:20:32,085
what would you two know about
the noble meaning of academic achievement?

221
00:20:32,169 --> 00:20:35,464
What would you know about
being ranked first in Haeseong?

222
00:20:35,547 --> 00:20:39,051
Going on about, "There's more to life
than grades," blah, blah, blah.

223
00:20:39,134 --> 00:20:41,845
A life of whining and excuses,
absent of any reflecting,

224
00:20:41,928 --> 00:20:44,598
is like putting your car in reverse
and flooring it.

225
00:20:44,681 --> 00:20:46,058
Reversing your whole life.

226
00:20:46,141 --> 00:20:47,642
You already live recklessly.

227
00:20:47,726 --> 00:20:49,394
How much further can you retreat?

228
00:20:49,478 --> 00:20:51,063
Your back's against the wall.

229
00:20:51,146 --> 00:20:52,898
Wait. Let go, Mr. Kang Ro-bin. Wait.

230
00:20:52,981 --> 00:20:54,024
Mr. Kang Ro-bin.

231
00:20:54,107 --> 00:20:55,442
Let go, please.

232
00:20:55,525 --> 00:20:57,152
Let go of me, you bastard!

233
00:20:58,111 --> 00:20:59,821
He's moved. This is how you're moved?

234
00:21:01,198 --> 00:21:02,240
Hey, Ro-bin.

235
00:21:02,324 --> 00:21:04,076
What's happening? I can't relax.

236
00:21:04,659 --> 00:21:07,371
-You'll break his hand.
-I can't let go. I'm sorry.

237
00:21:10,082 --> 00:21:11,583
Mr. Kang Ro-bin.

238
00:21:11,666 --> 00:21:13,502
Hey, get my hand off.

239
00:21:13,585 --> 00:21:14,669
Get it off!

240
00:21:16,588 --> 00:21:18,173
What's up with them?

241
00:21:18,256 --> 00:21:19,716
Let go!

242
00:21:21,385 --> 00:21:23,387
Oh my.

243
00:21:23,887 --> 00:21:26,848
My goodness,
why is there a bunny tail on her butt?

244
00:21:27,891 --> 00:21:28,725
Oh my.

245
00:21:31,103 --> 00:21:32,104
Huge.

246
00:21:33,688 --> 00:21:35,107
How unsightly.

247
00:21:36,566 --> 00:21:39,986
Well, they're not leaving much
to the imagination,

248
00:21:40,070 --> 00:21:42,030
so it's not thrilling at all.

249
00:21:42,781 --> 00:21:43,615
Oh my.

250
00:21:44,866 --> 00:21:46,660
Oh my.

251
00:21:47,702 --> 00:21:50,247
Hey, get my hand off, seriously!

252
00:21:52,249 --> 00:21:53,542
Cockroach!

253
00:21:54,418 --> 00:21:56,253
-Cockroach? Where?
-Where?

254
00:21:56,753 --> 00:21:58,797
Cockroach.

255
00:21:58,880 --> 00:22:01,466
Where is it? Where?

256
00:22:01,550 --> 00:22:03,969
Okay, I've never ranked first place
in anything!

257
00:22:07,264 --> 00:22:08,598
-Cockroach.
-Where is it?

258
00:22:12,978 --> 00:22:15,355
Calm down. Where is it?

259
00:22:15,439 --> 00:22:16,606
Where?

260
00:22:44,843 --> 00:22:46,511
What's so funny?

261
00:22:48,889 --> 00:22:51,892
What are you doing there
with those people?

262
00:22:55,896 --> 00:22:58,315
Hey, calm down. Where is it?

263
00:23:01,443 --> 00:23:02,652
It's gone again.

264
00:23:14,080 --> 00:23:15,123
No!

265
00:23:16,917 --> 00:23:19,211
Hey, Master, do something.

266
00:23:19,294 --> 00:23:21,755
There are too many cockroaches.

267
00:23:39,231 --> 00:23:40,982
Why are you back in Haeseong?

268
00:23:42,484 --> 00:23:44,236
To also find the Child of Eternity?

269
00:23:45,445 --> 00:23:46,279
Seok Ho-ran?

270
00:23:47,864 --> 00:23:48,823
Tell me.

271
00:23:50,116 --> 00:23:53,787
What are you doing here with those losers?
Why are you avoiding us?

272
00:23:54,538 --> 00:23:56,164
Our views are different now.

273
00:23:56,957 --> 00:23:57,916
And so are our paths.

274
00:23:58,542 --> 00:24:00,085
Are you mad because of Pal-ho?

275
00:24:01,086 --> 00:24:02,003
Why are you there

276
00:24:02,921 --> 00:24:04,256
with those people?

277
00:24:04,339 --> 00:24:06,091
Because they're family.

278
00:24:06,883 --> 00:24:09,386
Can't you tell
by how Father came back for us?

279
00:24:10,262 --> 00:24:11,096
Do you

280
00:24:12,681 --> 00:24:14,849
still call that man Father?

281
00:24:14,933 --> 00:24:17,185
Father still loves us.

282
00:24:17,269 --> 00:24:19,396
He experimented on us and used us.

283
00:24:20,063 --> 00:24:21,606
Out of need, not love.

284
00:24:21,690 --> 00:24:25,527
He said he'd make us better. That's why
he's searching for the Child of Eternity.

285
00:24:29,239 --> 00:24:30,740
Is that what you want to believe?

286
00:24:32,993 --> 00:24:34,411
Then keep living that way.

287
00:24:36,121 --> 00:24:39,583
Do you think you're something
after playing teacher to a few idiots?

288
00:24:40,166 --> 00:24:42,002
You don't have a clue!

289
00:24:45,171 --> 00:24:47,382
I made her up, you know.

290
00:24:48,341 --> 00:24:50,093
The mom you saw in your dreams.

291
00:24:50,677 --> 00:24:53,638
Every night, you kept crying,
calling for your mom,

292
00:24:53,722 --> 00:24:56,099
so I felt bad for you. Pitied you!

293
00:24:56,182 --> 00:24:58,268
I'm the one who was there to comfort you.

294
00:25:00,520 --> 00:25:01,730
But you're walking away?

295
00:25:01,813 --> 00:25:03,940
You want to stay with those losers?

296
00:25:04,024 --> 00:25:06,860
You'll die if you do.
Are you okay with that?

297
00:25:13,658 --> 00:25:14,492
Yeah.

298
00:25:24,669 --> 00:25:27,422
How can this be happening?

299
00:25:27,505 --> 00:25:28,798
A giant cockroach!

300
00:25:32,260 --> 00:25:33,178
Cockroach!

301
00:25:39,601 --> 00:25:41,811
Die, you bastard!

302
00:25:56,910 --> 00:25:58,578
Master! Are you okay?

303
00:25:58,662 --> 00:25:59,996
Where did the cockroaches go?

304
00:26:01,331 --> 00:26:02,332
What on earth…

305
00:26:03,124 --> 00:26:05,085
Where did the cockroaches go?

306
00:26:06,086 --> 00:26:07,379
The cockroaches…

307
00:26:24,020 --> 00:26:25,438
<i>A Wunderkinder did it?</i>

308
00:26:27,857 --> 00:26:30,151
Why did she come all the way there?

309
00:26:30,652 --> 00:26:32,570
Maybe she was bored and came to play.

310
00:26:35,615 --> 00:26:38,076
She came to see
if I found the Child of Eternity.

311
00:26:39,160 --> 00:26:40,328
The Child of Eternity?

312
00:26:41,663 --> 00:26:43,581
The only successful Wunderkinder.

313
00:26:44,124 --> 00:26:47,794
The child doesn't die…
because their heart doesn't stop.

314
00:26:49,379 --> 00:26:51,256
What an amazing heart they've got.

315
00:26:52,966 --> 00:26:56,177
I wanted to find the child first
before those guys did.

316
00:26:57,595 --> 00:26:58,430
But

317
00:26:59,848 --> 00:27:02,350
I'm not sure if finding them
is the right thing to do.

318
00:27:03,435 --> 00:27:06,146
I wonder if I'm exposing them
to more danger.

319
00:27:07,313 --> 00:27:10,066
Maybe I should have just let them
live in hiding.

320
00:27:10,150 --> 00:27:12,777
Well, first things first,
find that friend of yours

321
00:27:12,861 --> 00:27:14,446
and ask them yourself.

322
00:27:14,529 --> 00:27:17,282
"Would you like me
to find you or not find you?"

323
00:27:19,701 --> 00:27:22,078
Since I've had no luck
despite searching so hard,

324
00:27:22,579 --> 00:27:24,539
I'm starting to think
they're already dead.

325
00:27:26,958 --> 00:27:30,503
Didn't you say just two minutes ago
that they can't die?

326
00:27:34,632 --> 00:27:37,093
To be precise,
it's not that they can't die.

327
00:27:38,136 --> 00:27:39,846
They die and come back to life.

328
00:27:41,264 --> 00:27:42,390
Like you, Ms. Chae-ni.

329
00:27:45,018 --> 00:27:47,645
But I'm just a half-dried squid.

330
00:27:48,229 --> 00:27:49,856
I only half-die.

331
00:27:50,440 --> 00:27:53,693
Back then,
your heart definitely stopped beating.

332
00:27:54,444 --> 00:27:55,528
Then it beat again.

333
00:27:57,447 --> 00:27:59,491
So it wasn't a near-death experience?

334
00:28:01,117 --> 00:28:02,619
I actually died?

335
00:28:04,287 --> 00:28:06,456
To be honest,
I was a bit suspicious at first.

336
00:28:07,624 --> 00:28:09,292
I wondered if that heart

337
00:28:09,918 --> 00:28:11,836
had gone to you, Ms. Eun Chae-ni.

338
00:28:13,046 --> 00:28:14,005
But…

339
00:28:14,881 --> 00:28:18,051
But how could I have
the heart of someone who never dies?

340
00:28:19,803 --> 00:28:21,554
If the heart was transplanted,

341
00:28:22,722 --> 00:28:23,807
it could be possible.

342
00:28:23,890 --> 00:28:24,933
Goodness me.

343
00:28:25,975 --> 00:28:28,019
You're actually being serious right now.

344
00:28:30,271 --> 00:28:31,397
Come on.

345
00:28:31,481 --> 00:28:35,944
Do I look like someone who would steal
the heart of a total stranger?

346
00:28:36,444 --> 00:28:39,280
Seriously? That's outrageous.

347
00:28:41,115 --> 00:28:42,700
Since your grandmother

348
00:28:43,952 --> 00:28:45,954
sponsored those experiments 20 years ago…

349
00:28:48,915 --> 00:28:53,086
I thought for a moment
something like that could have happened.

350
00:28:56,589 --> 00:28:58,091
If not, I apologize

351
00:28:58,591 --> 00:29:00,093
for suspecting you.

352
00:29:03,263 --> 00:29:04,305
Just now…

353
00:29:04,806 --> 00:29:06,057
What did you…

354
00:29:06,724 --> 00:29:08,226
What did you say

355
00:29:09,060 --> 00:29:10,186
my grandma did?

356
00:29:11,980 --> 00:29:13,231
The person

357
00:29:14,274 --> 00:29:16,818
who sponsored
Dr. Ha Won-do's experiments 20 years ago…

358
00:29:19,070 --> 00:29:20,613
was King Jeon-bok of Myeong-dong.

359
00:29:28,538 --> 00:29:30,290
Aren't you overcooking them?

360
00:29:30,373 --> 00:29:32,250
-Should I turn it off?
-Turn it off, kid.

361
00:29:33,042 --> 00:29:35,795
Here, eat first. Have some <i>ramyeon </i>first.

362
00:29:35,879 --> 00:29:38,172
Let's eat.

363
00:29:43,303 --> 00:29:44,929
-Guess they're gone, huh?
-Yeah.

364
00:29:45,013 --> 00:29:46,180
-Let's eat.
-Okay.

365
00:29:53,980 --> 00:29:55,565
Did you not put in the noodles?

366
00:30:07,827 --> 00:30:10,121
You're home? What about dinner?

367
00:30:11,789 --> 00:30:13,374
Why are you just standing there?

368
00:30:14,083 --> 00:30:15,168
Grandma.

369
00:30:16,836 --> 00:30:18,421
What kind of surgery did I get?

370
00:30:23,217 --> 00:30:25,970
It was just a normal heart surgery, right?

371
00:30:26,471 --> 00:30:27,305
Right?

372
00:30:28,681 --> 00:30:29,849
Why are you

373
00:30:30,767 --> 00:30:32,352
asking all of a sudden?

374
00:30:36,981 --> 00:30:38,149
Because…

375
00:30:42,820 --> 00:30:43,863
Grandma.

376
00:30:45,198 --> 00:30:46,658
Listen and don't be shocked.

377
00:30:47,909 --> 00:30:48,910
I…

378
00:30:50,787 --> 00:30:51,621
died.

379
00:30:54,791 --> 00:30:56,876
But I came back to life.

380
00:30:58,711 --> 00:31:00,463
I thought I'd just dozed off,

381
00:31:00,964 --> 00:31:02,048
but that wasn't it.

382
00:31:03,466 --> 00:31:04,884
I died and came back to life.

383
00:31:08,972 --> 00:31:10,223
Why am I like this?

384
00:31:12,141 --> 00:31:13,101
Grandma.

385
00:31:14,519 --> 00:31:16,646
The surgery I had when I was seven…

386
00:31:18,982 --> 00:31:19,816
What was it?

387
00:31:34,789 --> 00:31:38,418
TOTAL REGENERATION OF PHYSICAL WOUNDS
REVIVES AFTER DEATH

388
00:31:49,178 --> 00:31:51,597
Okay. Three, two, one.

389
00:31:52,515 --> 00:31:53,891
Is anyone there?

390
00:31:53,975 --> 00:31:56,310
-Three, two, one.
-Coming through!

391
00:31:59,397 --> 00:32:00,815
Three, two, one!

392
00:32:27,759 --> 00:32:29,010
Was he dead?

393
00:32:31,804 --> 00:32:32,764
No.

394
00:32:57,747 --> 00:32:58,915
<i>He was killed</i>

395
00:33:00,041 --> 00:33:01,459
<i>for his own sake.</i>

396
00:33:02,001 --> 00:33:05,797
Over half of his brain was lost,
so he can't be revived anyway.

397
00:33:06,339 --> 00:33:09,926
Damage can be repaired,
but lost brain tissue can't be recovered.

398
00:33:10,843 --> 00:33:13,679
We need to transplant that heart
into someone else.

399
00:33:16,808 --> 00:33:18,518
It would be for the child's sake.

400
00:33:20,394 --> 00:33:22,688
We can't leave him like that forever.

401
00:33:46,087 --> 00:33:47,588
Three, two, one.

402
00:34:08,359 --> 00:34:09,193
Scalpel.

403
00:34:47,398 --> 00:34:49,358
HAESEONG DAILY
OCTOBER 1-31, 1979

404
00:34:58,034 --> 00:34:59,994
FIRE AT ORPHANAGE IN HAESEONG

405
00:35:04,874 --> 00:35:07,668
OVER 100 CHILDREN CONFINED
AT LEAST 50 PRESUMED DEAD

406
00:35:10,838 --> 00:35:12,882
THE UGLY TRUTH BEHIND DR. HA WON-DO

407
00:35:49,210 --> 00:35:50,920
I'm sorry.

408
00:35:51,712 --> 00:35:52,672
I'm sorry.

409
00:36:05,351 --> 00:36:06,477
I'm sorry.

410
00:36:24,370 --> 00:36:25,830
I'm sorry.

411
00:36:26,497 --> 00:36:27,623
I'm sorry.

412
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:32,628
What happened to Master was all my fault.

413
00:36:34,463 --> 00:36:36,674
I'm so very sorry.

414
00:36:38,676 --> 00:36:40,261
I'm sorry to everyone.

415
00:36:42,221 --> 00:36:43,806
I didn't deserve…

416
00:36:45,016 --> 00:36:46,976
All because of me…

417
00:36:49,478 --> 00:36:50,896
I'm sorry.

418
00:38:48,722 --> 00:38:49,765
Should I try

419
00:38:50,433 --> 00:38:51,642
talking to Chae-ni?

420
00:38:52,435 --> 00:38:54,311
Whatever you say to her,

421
00:38:54,812 --> 00:38:57,022
she won't be willing to listen.

422
00:39:05,322 --> 00:39:06,282
And you're sure

423
00:39:07,366 --> 00:39:09,285
the blood patch was human blood?

424
00:39:09,994 --> 00:39:10,953
Yes, Grandma.

425
00:39:11,620 --> 00:39:13,998
We'd best dig deeper into this, Jun-mo.

426
00:39:14,498 --> 00:39:16,876
I need to know

427
00:39:17,501 --> 00:39:19,044
what they're up to over there.

428
00:39:23,382 --> 00:39:24,216
Hey.

429
00:39:25,217 --> 00:39:26,510
Doesn't even say hi.

430
00:39:27,011 --> 00:39:27,928
Where's Ms. Chae-ni?

431
00:39:28,512 --> 00:39:29,346
Sorry?

432
00:39:30,139 --> 00:39:31,015
I don't know.

433
00:39:31,098 --> 00:39:32,975
She won't reply when I talk to her.

434
00:39:33,058 --> 00:39:34,977
She just lies there with her back turned.

435
00:39:36,020 --> 00:39:38,105
Can't you bump up our hourly rate?

436
00:39:38,189 --> 00:39:42,276
My Mi-hui keeps telling me to scrap
my sense of duty and just deliver flowers.

437
00:39:42,359 --> 00:39:44,987
So Ms. Eun Chae-ni has been home
the entire time?

438
00:39:45,070 --> 00:39:46,071
Yes.

439
00:39:46,697 --> 00:39:49,950
Except she's doing all that
at my place, not hers.

440
00:39:50,034 --> 00:39:52,328
Honestly, what's gotten into her?

441
00:39:52,828 --> 00:39:54,038
Did you hear me or what?

442
00:39:54,622 --> 00:39:55,789
Hey, you!

443
00:39:56,999 --> 00:40:00,211
Goddammit, what the hell did you eat?

444
00:40:16,227 --> 00:40:19,104
HAESEONG MILLENNIUM FIREWORKS FESTIVAL
DECEMBER 31, 1999

445
00:40:28,822 --> 00:40:31,659
Master! Here, <i>bungeo-ppang</i>.

446
00:40:32,826 --> 00:40:33,661
Here, they're hot.

447
00:40:33,744 --> 00:40:34,703
It's hot.

448
00:40:35,204 --> 00:40:37,456
<i>Miracles shall come to those who believe.</i>

449
00:40:42,419 --> 00:40:47,174
The marked one who will lead us
to salvation and eternal life,

450
00:40:47,258 --> 00:40:51,095
our shepherd Kim Pal-ho,
will now deliver his sermon!

451
00:41:12,074 --> 00:41:13,993
-One, two!
-<i>Taekwon</i>!

452
00:41:14,076 --> 00:41:15,035
Have a nice day.

453
00:41:15,119 --> 00:41:21,375
-One, two!
-<i>Taekwon</i>!

454
00:41:21,458 --> 00:41:24,545
-One, two!
-<i>Taekwon</i>!

455
00:41:27,631 --> 00:41:30,551
Come to the fireworks festival. Hello.

456
00:41:30,634 --> 00:41:32,011
Hello.

457
00:41:36,140 --> 00:41:38,559
Hurry up and hand them out
so we can get home!

458
00:41:38,642 --> 00:41:40,728
I can't separate them with these on.

459
00:41:40,811 --> 00:41:42,354
Then take your gloves off.

460
00:43:15,489 --> 00:43:16,407
Do you want some?

461
00:43:34,758 --> 00:43:36,343
That'll be 1,250 won.

462
00:43:48,772 --> 00:43:50,274
I thought long and hard,

463
00:43:50,774 --> 00:43:52,484
but I just couldn't figure out

464
00:43:53,235 --> 00:43:55,362
what to do in a situation like this.

465
00:43:57,948 --> 00:44:01,869
My grandma is the wisest,
most upright person

466
00:44:02,369 --> 00:44:04,079
in the world.

467
00:44:05,831 --> 00:44:08,167
But for her to have done
something like that…

468
00:44:10,252 --> 00:44:12,129
All because of me.

469
00:44:15,007 --> 00:44:16,717
I considered turning a blind eye,

470
00:44:17,426 --> 00:44:19,052
pretending I had no clue

471
00:44:20,345 --> 00:44:22,723
and acting like nothing happened.

472
00:44:24,892 --> 00:44:26,101
But

473
00:44:26,769 --> 00:44:29,438
that wouldn't mean anything actually did.

474
00:44:33,025 --> 00:44:35,444
That heart became my heart,

475
00:44:36,695 --> 00:44:39,406
and here I am, alive and well.

476
00:44:44,036 --> 00:44:45,996
I never chose

477
00:44:47,414 --> 00:44:48,874
to live the way I am.

478
00:44:51,335 --> 00:44:53,504
Just like you didn't choose

479
00:44:54,379 --> 00:44:55,923
to be the way you are.

480
00:44:58,467 --> 00:45:00,844
So don't think too hard about it.

481
00:45:01,762 --> 00:45:02,971
I know from experience

482
00:45:04,223 --> 00:45:06,558
that it doesn't help you
find the right answer.

483
00:45:09,394 --> 00:45:10,771
What should I do, then?

484
00:45:15,984 --> 00:45:17,611
You won't be able to meet

485
00:45:19,071 --> 00:45:20,864
that friend of yours.

486
00:45:29,706 --> 00:45:31,041
I'm sorry.

487
00:45:40,092 --> 00:45:41,593
Hey, Chae-ni!

488
00:45:45,722 --> 00:45:46,557
These.

489
00:45:49,726 --> 00:45:51,228
Chae-ni.

490
00:45:51,311 --> 00:45:54,565
Your grandma told me
to make sure you eat all of this.

491
00:45:55,274 --> 00:45:56,608
I told her,

492
00:45:56,692 --> 00:45:59,736
"Since you're here, why don't you
at least see her before you go?"

493
00:45:59,820 --> 00:46:03,824
But she said, "No. As long as my Eunie
is doing well, that's all that matters."

494
00:46:03,907 --> 00:46:05,075
You should…

495
00:46:22,009 --> 00:46:23,010
Chae-ni.

496
00:46:43,697 --> 00:46:46,491
Because I have so many sins,

497
00:46:47,826 --> 00:46:49,870
because my sins are so great…

498
00:46:53,624 --> 00:46:56,919
I made my baby go through so much pain.

499
00:47:27,282 --> 00:47:29,409
I can't condone what you did, Grandma,

500
00:47:30,869 --> 00:47:33,205
because what you did was truly terrible.

501
00:47:34,706 --> 00:47:35,624
Right.

502
00:47:40,379 --> 00:47:42,089
I don't expect you to.

503
00:47:42,172 --> 00:47:43,465
But I can…

504
00:47:45,759 --> 00:47:47,511
stand with you if people throw stones.

505
00:47:47,594 --> 00:47:48,762
Right.

506
00:47:52,057 --> 00:47:54,184
We can atone for your sins

507
00:47:54,768 --> 00:47:56,895
and beg for forgiveness together.

508
00:47:58,355 --> 00:47:59,815
It's only natural.

509
00:48:03,610 --> 00:48:04,444
Right.

510
00:48:05,195 --> 00:48:06,363
So, from now on,

511
00:48:07,114 --> 00:48:08,657
I'll try to live life…

512
00:48:11,118 --> 00:48:12,411
to the fullest.

513
00:48:14,705 --> 00:48:16,081
If I don't,

514
00:48:17,124 --> 00:48:18,750
I think I'll feel guilty

515
00:48:19,710 --> 00:48:21,545
toward the owner of my heart

516
00:48:22,129 --> 00:48:23,755
and the other kids.

517
00:48:26,508 --> 00:48:27,342
Right.

518
00:48:29,094 --> 00:48:30,095
So…

519
00:48:33,056 --> 00:48:34,558
I need a little time.

520
00:48:41,064 --> 00:48:42,399
I'm proud of you, my baby.

521
00:48:43,859 --> 00:48:45,986
Did you eat all of this in one day?

522
00:48:46,069 --> 00:48:48,196
You're impressive, as always.

523
00:48:51,324 --> 00:48:54,036
Well, of course.
I hadn't eaten a thing all day.

524
00:48:54,119 --> 00:48:58,206
From now on,
I'm going to live life to the full,

525
00:48:58,749 --> 00:49:00,042
so I can't go hungry.

526
00:49:05,047 --> 00:49:07,049
<i>Sure, giving it your all is great.</i>

527
00:49:07,674 --> 00:49:09,885
But why are you doing that here?

528
00:49:11,011 --> 00:49:13,764
Well, things are still
a little awkward with Grandma.

529
00:49:14,890 --> 00:49:15,766
And what about you?

530
00:49:15,849 --> 00:49:17,184
It's dangerous

531
00:49:17,684 --> 00:49:20,187
for an adult man
and a woman to be alone all night.

532
00:49:20,270 --> 00:49:21,354
You know it.

533
00:49:21,980 --> 00:49:24,274
Dangerous for whom? For me?

534
00:49:26,902 --> 00:49:30,280
Come on. It'll be more fun to train
while living together. Right, Master?

535
00:49:31,573 --> 00:49:32,699
Come lie down here.

536
00:49:37,662 --> 00:49:40,290
You leave tomorrow.
I'm not letting you stay any longer.

537
00:49:57,015 --> 00:50:00,227
Should I be relieved
that Mr. Son isn't here too, at least?

538
00:50:09,027 --> 00:50:12,614
We need a table or something.
Every meal is so uncomfortable.

539
00:50:12,697 --> 00:50:14,157
Thank you for the food.

540
00:50:14,241 --> 00:50:15,283
Dig in.

541
00:50:19,246 --> 00:50:20,580
-It's hot!
-It's hot!

542
00:50:22,332 --> 00:50:23,166
Hello?

543
00:50:23,250 --> 00:50:26,837
I booked a cleaning job at 1:00 p.m.
at the container park. Meet me there.

544
00:50:27,963 --> 00:50:30,173
A training session
disguised as a cleaning job?

545
00:50:30,257 --> 00:50:33,468
Okay, got it.
I'll tell Ro-bin and Mr. Son too.

546
00:50:35,095 --> 00:50:36,179
You're together?

547
00:50:37,055 --> 00:50:37,889
Yes.

548
00:50:38,723 --> 00:50:39,558
Where?

549
00:50:44,062 --> 00:50:47,691
See you later.

550
00:50:48,191 --> 00:50:49,276
You're good at that.

551
00:50:50,068 --> 00:50:53,155
Make sure you hide your stuff well,
especially things like this.

552
00:50:53,238 --> 00:50:55,323
If he finds these,
we'll be caught red-handed.

553
00:50:55,407 --> 00:50:56,408
-Hide them well.
-Okay.

554
00:50:56,491 --> 00:50:58,034
And make sure to do the dishes.

555
00:50:58,118 --> 00:50:59,494
Got it.

556
00:50:59,995 --> 00:51:02,998
We can't leave a single trace.
And let's hurry.

557
00:51:14,176 --> 00:51:15,302
I guess it's true.

558
00:51:15,385 --> 00:51:17,345
It works when my feelings are hurt.

559
00:51:19,264 --> 00:51:21,266
But isn't that too cruel?

560
00:51:21,349 --> 00:51:25,687
Isn't it bad if I need to hear mean things
to activate my powers?

561
00:51:27,689 --> 00:51:30,817
What about you, Mr. Son?
Still don't know your secret switch?

562
00:51:30,901 --> 00:51:34,029
No, I'm not sure yet.

563
00:51:36,364 --> 00:51:37,282
What the…

564
00:51:38,366 --> 00:51:39,201
What was that?

565
00:51:40,744 --> 00:51:42,329
I think you just lied.

566
00:51:42,913 --> 00:51:46,541
Lied? No, I didn't.
What do you mean I lied? I didn't!

567
00:51:46,625 --> 00:51:48,919
This is dusty.
I'd better go shake the dust out.

568
00:51:55,133 --> 00:51:56,218
It's true.

569
00:51:56,718 --> 00:51:57,552
You liar.

570
00:52:05,227 --> 00:52:07,646
Well, aren't you as sharp as a hawk?

571
00:52:11,441 --> 00:52:14,903
Running or being breathless doesn't work,
and you don't even get startled,

572
00:52:14,986 --> 00:52:18,740
so you need to think of other ways,
not just wait around for it to happen.

573
00:52:20,116 --> 00:52:23,286
Find out whether your trigger
is an emotion, a word, or an action.

574
00:52:25,497 --> 00:52:28,792
Wow, Mr. Oddball has quite the temper.

575
00:52:28,875 --> 00:52:30,126
-Excuse me.
-He's cool.

576
00:52:30,210 --> 00:52:31,294
Ms. Eun Chae-ni?

577
00:52:31,920 --> 00:52:32,754
Ms. Eun Chae-ni!

578
00:52:32,837 --> 00:52:35,465
For goodness' sake.

579
00:52:35,548 --> 00:52:38,927
So people really do show their true colors
when teaching you to drive.

580
00:52:39,010 --> 00:52:40,011
Why are you so mad?

581
00:52:40,095 --> 00:52:42,806
'Cause instead of trying,
you're just sitting there all anxious.

582
00:52:43,765 --> 00:52:45,141
Man, I'm parched!

583
00:52:51,773 --> 00:52:53,441
Do you think I want to mope around?

584
00:52:53,525 --> 00:52:54,359
Hey!

585
00:52:54,442 --> 00:52:55,819
You can't have caffeine.

586
00:52:57,529 --> 00:52:58,363
Oh, right.

587
00:53:03,660 --> 00:53:04,786
I'm fine.

588
00:53:08,999 --> 00:53:11,459
What the…
Hey, I can hear that from over here.

589
00:53:16,172 --> 00:53:19,884
<i>All across the country we go</i>

590
00:53:19,968 --> 00:53:22,178
<i>Let's go!</i>

591
00:53:22,887 --> 00:53:25,181
-What the heck was that?
-<i>Take the bus, leave Seoul</i>

592
00:53:25,265 --> 00:53:27,392
<i>To Gangwon State</i>
<i>Seoraksan, Yangyang, Naksansa</i>

593
00:53:27,475 --> 00:53:29,561
<i>Over Daegwallyeong Pass</i>
<i>Gangneung Gyeongpodae</i>

594
00:53:29,644 --> 00:53:31,229
<i>Samcheok, Chokseokru</i>
<i>Ulleungdo, Seonginbong</i>

595
00:53:31,313 --> 00:53:33,857
-<i>Tired from Taebaeksan</i>
-What the heck?

596
00:53:33,940 --> 00:53:35,525
<i>On to Chungcheong-do</i>

597
00:53:35,608 --> 00:53:38,111
<i>Through the winding islands</i>

598
00:53:38,194 --> 00:53:40,071
<i>Jeju, full of haenyeo</i>

599
00:53:40,155 --> 00:53:42,532
<i>Off to Gyeongsang-do</i>

600
00:53:43,408 --> 00:53:45,577
<i>So much to see in Gyeongju</i>

601
00:53:45,660 --> 00:53:47,871
<i>Bulguksa, Dabotap</i>
<i>Seokgatap, Cheomseongdae</i>

602
00:53:47,954 --> 00:53:49,706
<i>Seokguram, Tohamsan at sunrise</i>

603
00:53:49,789 --> 00:53:51,833
<i>Ulsan factory tours</i>

604
00:53:51,916 --> 00:53:53,918
<i>Pohang Beach, the steel mills</i>

605
00:53:54,002 --> 00:53:55,879
<i>The express bus to Seoul awaits</i>

606
00:53:55,962 --> 00:53:58,214
<i>My legs and back hurt</i>

607
00:53:58,298 --> 00:53:59,966
<i>Oh dear, oh dear</i>

608
00:54:00,050 --> 00:54:02,844
<i>That was a good tour</i>

609
00:54:04,596 --> 00:54:07,766
Good thinking,
buying this wild ginseng wine.

610
00:54:11,478 --> 00:54:14,189
Caffeine… effective.

611
00:54:17,567 --> 00:54:20,445
Get up, Ms. Eun Chae-ni.
Let's move on to the next step.

612
00:54:23,948 --> 00:54:27,035
Get on up, Ms. Eun Chae-ni.
Let's move on to the next step.

613
00:54:28,661 --> 00:54:32,332
Let's see how much caffeine you need
and if you can easily take others along.

614
00:54:32,916 --> 00:54:34,542
If you can hold someone's hand--

615
00:54:39,381 --> 00:54:43,093
Man, my eyes are so dry
from all the wind she's kicking up.

616
00:54:43,718 --> 00:54:46,262
Deary me.

617
00:54:46,346 --> 00:54:48,348
It's so nice and peaceful--

618
00:54:48,848 --> 00:54:49,974
Back already?

619
00:54:50,475 --> 00:54:52,227
Chae-ni, where's Master?

620
00:54:54,104 --> 00:54:55,939
We need to be touching to go together.

621
00:54:57,023 --> 00:54:59,150
Why'd he get so annoyed?
We can just try it.

622
00:54:59,234 --> 00:55:01,444
Okay, and where is Master?

623
00:55:01,528 --> 00:55:04,656
I'm starting to get sick of him.
Should I just leave him there?

624
00:55:04,739 --> 00:55:05,657
What?

625
00:55:10,370 --> 00:55:12,705
-Hello--
<i>-You better not leave me here by myself.</i>

626
00:55:15,458 --> 00:55:16,751
I swear he's inside my--

627
00:55:19,963 --> 00:55:20,880
Got any eye drops?

628
00:55:21,589 --> 00:55:22,424
None.

629
00:55:35,812 --> 00:55:37,147
Hey, Master!

630
00:55:37,647 --> 00:55:38,982
Here!

631
00:55:43,027 --> 00:55:46,364
So I guess we need to be touching
for us to travel together.

632
00:55:46,448 --> 00:55:48,116
Wait there.

633
00:55:48,825 --> 00:55:50,410
Don't go anywhere.

634
00:55:52,245 --> 00:55:53,496
Come here.

635
00:55:54,038 --> 00:55:55,498
Okay!

636
00:56:17,020 --> 00:56:19,063
Master!

637
00:56:27,614 --> 00:56:28,781
Grab on!

638
00:56:44,964 --> 00:56:46,257
Hello?

639
00:56:54,432 --> 00:56:55,475
I'll be right there!

640
00:57:26,172 --> 00:57:28,341
I'll just take an intercity bus.

641
00:57:29,425 --> 00:57:30,301
Go.

642
00:57:30,969 --> 00:57:32,095
Just go.

643
00:57:32,595 --> 00:57:36,891
I guess I don't always land
in the same spot.

644
00:57:37,392 --> 00:57:38,977
It's totally random!

645
00:58:07,380 --> 00:58:08,423
Master!

646
00:58:09,257 --> 00:58:11,259
Ms. Eun Chae-ni!

647
00:58:40,079 --> 00:58:43,166
You're really putting me off
working with you. This looks fine.

648
00:58:43,249 --> 00:58:44,751
You talk too much, punk.

649
00:58:45,251 --> 00:58:47,337
Look. It's laid out nicely.

650
00:58:49,464 --> 00:58:51,591
Master! You're back.

651
00:58:52,091 --> 00:58:53,176
That was fast.

652
00:58:59,057 --> 00:59:01,434
What are you doing?

653
00:59:02,268 --> 00:59:05,813
Let's eat together.
Chae-ni's been talking about it for days.

654
00:59:06,773 --> 00:59:07,607
Why?

655
00:59:09,108 --> 00:59:09,942
Your birthday.

656
00:59:10,818 --> 00:59:13,696
It's not any time soon.
And it's not even my real birthday.

657
00:59:15,365 --> 00:59:16,532
A party to celebrate your

658
00:59:17,325 --> 00:59:18,409
two-month pre-birthday.

659
00:59:19,035 --> 00:59:20,328
Who even celebrates that?

660
00:59:21,996 --> 00:59:24,415
Does a party have to be something special?

661
00:59:24,916 --> 00:59:27,460
If we throw one and it's fun,
it's a party.

662
00:59:27,543 --> 00:59:29,337
You can have a party two months before,

663
00:59:29,420 --> 00:59:31,839
one month before,
and on your actual birthday.

664
00:59:32,423 --> 00:59:33,675
Even a month after.

665
00:59:34,509 --> 00:59:35,343
I guess,

666
00:59:36,177 --> 00:59:38,680
if you feel like it,
we could even have one every day.

667
00:59:39,889 --> 00:59:40,723
Why?

668
00:59:41,391 --> 00:59:44,811
We thought you would've eaten alone,
slept alone,

669
00:59:44,894 --> 00:59:48,231
watched TV alone, and so on, Master.

670
00:59:49,232 --> 00:59:50,692
Now we'll do all that with you.

671
00:59:56,322 --> 00:59:59,534
Mr. Son, I thought you would
at least have more sense.

672
01:00:00,451 --> 01:00:02,495
I have plenty of sense.

673
01:00:02,578 --> 01:00:06,290
But Chae-ni said she'd give me her wage,
so I'm attending for business purposes.

674
01:00:06,374 --> 01:00:08,876
I have no personal feelings
about this at all.

675
01:00:09,794 --> 01:00:12,296
I hope that you are never lonely

676
01:00:12,380 --> 01:00:14,716
and wish you a lifetime of happiness.

677
01:00:15,717 --> 01:00:17,051
For you, Master,

678
01:00:17,719 --> 01:00:18,553
and for us.

679
01:00:20,096 --> 01:00:20,930
Yeah.

680
01:00:21,431 --> 01:00:24,225
Starting today, every day.

681
01:00:33,317 --> 01:00:34,569
Hey, what time is it?

682
01:00:35,069 --> 01:00:38,906
The bakery's about to close.
Who's going to go buy the cake?

683
01:00:52,086 --> 01:00:53,838
Why didn't you buy it on your way in?

684
01:00:53,921 --> 01:00:57,508
Goodness, are you a young master
from a rich family?

685
01:00:57,592 --> 01:01:00,136
You have to go near closing time
to get one on clearance.

686
01:01:01,804 --> 01:01:02,930
Wait, did you come

687
01:01:03,765 --> 01:01:04,891
to pick me up?

688
01:01:10,521 --> 01:01:12,899
About your mom, Master.

689
01:01:13,399 --> 01:01:15,693
So she's not dead,
just living away from you?

690
01:01:15,777 --> 01:01:17,028
Where does she live?

691
01:01:18,029 --> 01:01:19,447
Why are you suddenly…

692
01:01:19,947 --> 01:01:21,282
The other day, in your sleep,

693
01:01:22,283 --> 01:01:23,618
you called for your mom.

694
01:01:24,660 --> 01:01:26,496
You cried, "Mom."

695
01:01:28,748 --> 01:01:29,665
Did I?

696
01:01:31,626 --> 01:01:34,337
I don't even know
if those memories are real.

697
01:01:34,837 --> 01:01:36,214
I lost my memories in the lab.

698
01:01:38,424 --> 01:01:41,219
A person who I think is my mom
appears in my dreams sometimes,

699
01:01:41,886 --> 01:01:44,263
but I can't see her face,
and I don't remember her.

700
01:01:45,640 --> 01:01:47,391
I don't even know my real name.

701
01:01:52,688 --> 01:01:54,774
Your face looks like you're thinking,

702
01:01:55,274 --> 01:01:56,818
"That's all my fault too."

703
01:01:58,903 --> 01:02:00,905
You, Master,

704
01:02:01,489 --> 01:02:02,949
and all your friends…

705
01:02:07,036 --> 01:02:09,205
I feel like it's all my fault.

706
01:02:09,288 --> 01:02:10,498
You know…

707
01:02:12,291 --> 01:02:16,420
where, how, and what you'll do,
and who you'll live to protect

708
01:02:16,921 --> 01:02:18,256
are for you to decide.

709
01:02:19,006 --> 01:02:20,383
Not someone else.

710
01:02:23,678 --> 01:02:24,929
Master,

711
01:02:25,596 --> 01:02:27,390
you really do seem like a master.

712
01:02:29,100 --> 01:02:30,893
You have so many teachings.

713
01:02:33,479 --> 01:02:37,149
You leave me with no choice
but to pledge my loyalty to you.

714
01:02:39,402 --> 01:02:42,572
I can't give you all of my life,

715
01:02:43,072 --> 01:02:46,200
but I'll give you about one tenth of it,
out of loyalty.

716
01:02:47,952 --> 01:02:49,996
Don't let people in so easily.

717
01:02:51,455 --> 01:02:53,457
And don't be fooled by shallow kindness.

718
01:02:57,420 --> 01:02:59,088
That way, though you may get lonely,

719
01:02:59,922 --> 01:03:00,965
you're never in danger.

720
01:03:04,093 --> 01:03:06,345
So that's how you've lived your life.

721
01:03:07,805 --> 01:03:10,433
If you still want to let someone in
despite all that,

722
01:03:10,933 --> 01:03:11,934
remember this.

723
01:03:13,060 --> 01:03:14,520
You need the courage to risk…

724
01:03:16,522 --> 01:03:19,150
your whole life, not just one tenth of it.

725
01:03:20,109 --> 01:03:22,278
Being by someone's side

726
01:03:22,778 --> 01:03:26,866
isn't as dangerous or as difficult
as you think.

727
01:03:28,034 --> 01:03:29,035
You just stay.

728
01:03:30,745 --> 01:03:32,288
It's such an easy thing,

729
01:03:32,955 --> 01:03:34,540
so why overcomplicate it?

730
01:03:37,335 --> 01:03:38,169
Because usually…

731
01:03:42,506 --> 01:03:43,716
you either use people…

732
01:03:45,426 --> 01:03:46,510
or end up being used.

733
01:04:42,692 --> 01:04:44,944
<i>She teleports when her heart beats fast.</i>

734
01:04:46,362 --> 01:04:48,155
<i>She doesn't scare easily,</i>

735
01:04:49,573 --> 01:04:50,700
<i>but if she's flustered</i>

736
01:04:51,367 --> 01:04:53,494
<i>or if she's set on doing</i>
<i>or not doing something,</i>

737
01:04:54,328 --> 01:04:58,040
<i>her heart starts to race, driven by</i>
<i>unpredictable emotions and moods,</i>

738
01:04:58,124 --> 01:04:59,458
<i>so don't let your guard down.</i>

739
01:05:00,584 --> 01:05:03,170
<i>She can also teleport objects and people,</i>
<i>so be careful.</i>

740
01:05:03,921 --> 01:05:07,133
<i>Even if she disappears,</i>
<i>she always returns,</i>

741
01:05:07,216 --> 01:05:08,759
<i>but not to the exact same spot.</i>

742
01:05:09,343 --> 01:05:12,430
<i>You should keep watch of the area</i>
<i>and be ready to capture her.</i>

743
01:05:15,725 --> 01:05:17,768
<i>As long as her heart doesn't beat fast,</i>

744
01:05:18,352 --> 01:05:20,146
<i>that woman can't do anything.</i>

745
01:05:40,332 --> 01:05:41,792
What will you do with her now?

746
01:05:43,669 --> 01:05:46,714
<i>Everything has its place and purpose.</i>

747
01:05:47,214 --> 01:05:49,800
<i>That heart doesn't belong to her.</i>

748
01:05:50,301 --> 01:05:51,927
<i>It should be returned to its place.</i>

749
01:05:56,724 --> 01:05:59,268
PERSONAL RECORD CARD
3972

750
01:05:59,351 --> 01:06:01,729
<i>Is there anything else we should know?</i>

751
01:06:02,229 --> 01:06:03,856
<i>Any precautions we should take?</i>

752
01:06:06,400 --> 01:06:07,443
No, there isn't.

753
01:06:37,223 --> 01:06:44,188
OUR MASTER
MAY YOU ALSO MASTER HAPPINESS

754
01:10:10,019 --> 01:10:15,024
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi

